   <!-- ================================================== -->
   <!--                 System Description                 -->
   <!-- ================================================== -->

   <gml:description>The Gill WindSonic has been developed specifically for use
as a low-cost alternative to traditional moving-parts wind
sensors and is suitable for use in onshore or offshore
environments.
The WindSonic is a lightweight, robust unit, completely
sealed and constructed in UV-resistance plastic. With a low
start-up speed (0.01m/s) and no moving parts, the Gill
anemometer exhibits significant benefits over standard 3-
cup and propeller anemometers. The WindSonic requires
no calibration or maintenance. Wind speed and direction
data is provided via a serial bi-directional link, and the
output may be configured by the user to provide a variety of
communication formats, including a choice of units of
measure and averaging periods. Sophisticated error
checking and a fault reporting system are supplied as
standard, ensuring the user’s confidence in the reported
data. The Gill WindSonic represents the best all weather
solution on the market for providing reliable and accurate
wind speed and direction information with virtually zero
maintenance.</gml:description>
